org.javact.compiler
Class SynchronousMessage

java.lang.Object
  org.javact.compiler.Message
      org.javact.compiler.SynchronousMessage

 class SynchronousMessage
extends Message

Class that implements the Message class and provides the handling of synchronous messages.
Note that the return type must either be a primitive type (int, boolean...) or a simple class type — not an array! (this is not yet implemented but might change in the future.)
The name of the return type is appended to the name of the message — thus the message get returning an Integer object will be implemented by a class named [JSM]getInteger. This will lead to a problem when return types coming from different packages have the same name. For example two getmessages returning respectively a foo.Type and a bar.Type object both will result in the same getType class. However this should be quite unusual.

Version:
0.5.0
Author:
Vincent Hennebert
